```

SlateOS is licensed under the GNU General Public License Version 3 (GPLv3).

You are free to:

* Use SlateOS for any purpose.
* Study how SlateOS works.
* Modify SlateOS to suit your needs.
* Share copies of SlateOS.
* Share modified versions of SlateOS.

If you distribute modified versions of SlateOS, you must:

* Make the source code available.
* License your modifications under the same GPLv3 license.
* Preserve copyright notices.
* Clearly state what changes were made.

You may not:

* Distribute a modified version of SlateOS as closed-source software.
* Remove the freedoms granted by this license.
* Prevent users from accessing the source code of distributed versions.

  ```
                     Privacy Statement
  ```

SlateOS is designed as a privacy-focused operating system.

The SlateOS project does not require telemetry, tracking, advertising systems, or mandatory online accounts.

Users remain in control of their own devices and data.

